@HEugeneWrites Yes, that makes sense. It helps to read the scene out loud when you're finished writing to ensure the word isn't overused.

@HEugeneWrites If two characters are arguing for example, words like "ordered" "yelled" "bellowed" "demanded" etc. work better...
@HEugeneWrites Obviously it depends on the scene, dialogue and characters. But said is overused. Yes, it's acceptable but sparingly.
@HEugeneWrites With a multitude of powerful words in the English language, the overuse of "said" drives me crazy! @Writestream
One of my pet peeves. LOL RT @HEugeneWrites: @thePenleak @Writestream Interesting as always.  Lots of debate about using the word said
